'''Autosadism''', or '''automasochism''', is behaviour inflicting [[pain]] or [[humiliation]] on oneself. It may be related to [[self-harm]]<ref>{{cite book | title=Clinical Assessment, Computerized Methods, and Instrumentation | first=Frans J. | last=Maarse| publisher=Taylor & Francis | year=2003 | isbn=90-265-1944-3 | page=78 }}</ref><ref>{{cite book | title=Autistic barriers in neurotic patients | first=Frances | last=Tustin |publisher=Karnac Books | year=1986 | isbn=0-946439-25-7 | page=60 }}</ref> or a [[paraphilia]] involving [[sexual arousal]].<ref>{{Harvnb|Aggrawal|2008|p=371}}</ref> It can be viewed as a form of [[Sadomasochism |masochism]],<ref>{{Harvnb|Aggrawal|2008|p=168}}</ref> a [[sublimation (psychology)|sublimated]] form of sadism, or a means to experiencing [[algolagnia]], a sexual tendency which is defined by deriving sexual pleasure and stimulation from physical pain.<ref>{{cite book | first=Havelock | last=Ellis | title=Studies in the Psychology of Sex | volume=3  | authorlink=Havelock Ellis | edition=3rd | publisher=Echo Library | year=2007 | isbn=1-4068-6282-7 | page=122 }}</ref>

