'''Nikhef''' is the Dutch National Institute for [[Subatomic]] [[Physics]] that performs research in [[particle physics]] and [[astroparticle physics]]. Amongst others, it is a research partner of the [[CERN]] institute in Switzerland,<ref name="about-us">{{cite web|url=https://www.nikhef.nl/en/about-nikhef/|title=About Nikhef|publisher=Nikhef|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref> and is a collaboration between [[Foundation for Fundamental Research on Matter]] (FOM), [[University of Amsterdam]], [[Vrije Universiteit Amsterdam]], [[Radboud University]], [[University of Groningen]], and [[Utrecht University]].<ref name="organisation">{{cite web|url=https://www.nikhef.nl/en/about-nikhef/organisation/|title=Organisation|publisher=Nikhef|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref> The current director is Stan Bentvelsen.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nikhef.nl/over-nikhef/organisatie/directorate/|title=Biografie/CV Prof. Dr. Stan Bentvelsen|publisher=Nikhef|language=Dutch|access-date=12 July 2014}}</ref> Nikhef is located at the [[Amsterdam Science Park]] in [[Watergraafsmeer]] in the [[Netherlands]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.amsterdamsciencepark.nl/science-meets-business/research-institutes/nikhef/|title=Nikhef/National Institute for Subatomic Physics|publisher=Amsterdam Science Park|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref>
NIKHEF is an acronym for ''Nationaal Instituut voor Kernfysica en Hoge-Energiefysica'' (National Institute for Nuclear and High energy physics). This acronym is no longer used and the name was changed to ''Nationaal instituut voor subatomaire fysica'' (National Institute for Subatomic Physics). The name Nikhef is preserved to maintain name recognition (now only with a capital N).<ref name="organisation" /><ref name="about-us" />
It also was the host of the third [[website]] in the world, starting in February 1992.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nic.nikhef.nl/~a03/www/default/NikhefGuide.html|title=The Nikhef website in 1992|publisher=Nikhef|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref> Nikhef is also one of the eight colocations of the [[Amsterdam Internet Exchange]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nikhef.nl/ams-ix/|title=Housing at Nikhef|publisher=Nikhef|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://ams-ix.net/connect-to-ams-ix/colocations|title=Colocations|publisher=Amsterdam Internet Exchange|access-date=14 July 2016}}</ref> [[Stan Bentvelsen]] is the director of Nikhef since December 1, 2014.<ref>https://www.nikhef.nl/over-nikhef/organisatie/directorate/</ref>
